  "text": "The relationship between sex hormones and bone health in general has been well documented, [CITATION_1] prompting the intriguing question of whether the large fluctuations of sex hormones during the menstrual cycle may have an acute impact on bone metabolism. Over the past 30 years, about a dozen studies have been published that examine this question. Although the results have been inconclusive, some data suggest that the cyclic changes in sex hormones may significantly affect bone metabolism during the normal ovulatory menstrual cycle.",
